Interventional techniques are used to stop bleeding which include:      Bronchial arterial embolization which is:        Considered as a first line therapy for both new and recurrent hemoptysis Less invasive and reliable procedure Operator-dependent technique Excellent outcome with immediate control of bleeding reaching 80-94%
{{#ev:youtube|kLO6UXaVb9w}} {{#ev:youtube|zJ85gIjGOzY}}
Other bronchoscopic strategies that are used to stop bleeding in a patient with hemoptysis include: Cold saline lavage Topical vasoconstrictor agents Balloon tamponade Endobronchial stent placement Endobronchial spigot Oxidized regenerated cellulose N-Butyl cyanoacrylate glue Fibrinogen thrombin Tranexamic acid Laser photocoagulation Argon plasma coagulation Electrocautery

The diagnosis is established by clinical findings and the detection of serum long chain fatty acid levels. 
Chromosome study to look for changes (mutations) in the ABCD1 gene. It is particularly reliable in carriers  and recommended as the diagnostic assay in women.

